FBIS4-62515 "drsov095_p_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 16 May 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Ter-Petrosyan Denounces Bomb Explosion at Tbilisi Theater Ter-Petrosyan Denounces Bomb Explosion at Tbilisi Theater LD1605182594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1704 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605182594 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] [Text] Yerevan 16 May TASS -- Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan expressed condolences to the families of the victims of the bomb explosion in the Armenian drama theater in Tbilisi on Sunday [15 May] that wounded 16 people. Ter-Petrosyan denounced the action as a "dreadful terroristic act" and a "provocation against traditional Armenian-Georgian friendship." The Armenian leader expressed the confidence that the accident will not affect relations between the two nations and that the Georgian authorities will take all necessary measures to find and punish the terrorists and prevent terroristic acts against the Armenians living in Georgia.
